#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h2>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:4
msgid "Quarkus is a proud member of the Commonhaus Foundation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:7
msgid "The Commonhaus Foundation which is a non-profit dedicated to the enduring viability of open-source projects. It offers a neutral environment, a governing structure, and assistance to projects, prioritizing their independence and development led by the community. They furnish resources such as legal aid, infrastructure, and financial avenues, all while honoring each project's established governance and culture."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:8
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://www.commonhaus.org/\" target=\"blank\">Learn more about the Commonhaus Foundation and how you can make a difference</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><a>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:11
msgid "<a href=\"https://www.commonhaus.org/\" target=\"blank\">"
msgstr ""

#. type: Attribute 'alt' of: <div><div><div><a><img><img>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:12 _includes/benefactors.html:13
msgid "Learn about the Commonhaus Foundation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:22
msgid "IBM"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:23
msgid "IBM strengthened its Java and Quarkus commitment by moving the Red Hat engineers working on Quarkus into IBM. This ensured dedicated resources for Quarkus's growth, deepening IBM's open-source involvement and focus on cloud-native Java for enterprises."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:24
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://www.ibm.com/opensource/\" target=\"blank\">Learn more about open source at IBM</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:27
msgid "Red Hat"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:28
msgid "Quarkus originated at Red Hat, which ensured its ongoing development and stability by employing many of its principal engineers. This support helped cultivate a strong ecosystem for cloud-native application development. A key reason for Quarkus's transition to the Commonhaus Foundation was Red Hat's dedication to its open-source nature."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:29
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://www.redhat.com/en/blog/what-does-open-source-program-office-do\" target=\"blank\">Learn more about open source at Red Hat</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:32
msgid "AWS"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:33
msgid "AWS aids Quarkus by donating credits, enabling developers to use AWS services for testing, CI, and feature development. This support accelerates Quarkus innovation, enhancing the cloud-native experience on AWS."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:34
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://aws.amazon.com/opensource/\" target=\"blank\">Learn more about open source at AWS</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:37
msgid "Github"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:38
msgid "GitHub's donation of GitHub Actions runners aids the Quarkus team by providing dedicated compute resources. This contribution eases infrastructure strain, accelerates development and testing, and boosts community collaboration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:39
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/actions/concepts/runners/github-hosted-runners\" target=\"blank\">Learn more about Github Action runners</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:42
msgid "RunsOn"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:43
msgid "Quarkus appreciates RunsOn’s contribution of a free key so the project can access their platform for managing and launching self-hosted GitHub Actions runners on Amazon Web Services (AWS) infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:44
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://runs-on.com/\" target=\"blank\"> Learn more about RunsOn</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:47
msgid "Gradle Technologies"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:48
msgid "Gradle Technologies significantly supports the Quarkus ecosystem by donating a Develocity instance. This donation offers Quarkus developers advanced build insights and performance analytics, optimizing build processes for faster debugging, improved reliability, and enhanced productivity."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:49
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://gradle.com/develocity/\" target=\"blank\"> Learn more about Develocity</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h3>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:52
msgid "Zulip"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:53
msgid "Zulip is an organized team chat app designed for efficient communication."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:54
msgid "<i class=\"fa fa-chevron-right\"></i><a href=\"https://zulip.com/\" target=\"blank\"> Learn more about Zulip</a>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><h2>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:60
msgid "Quarkus Extension Benefactors"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:61
msgid "In the Quarkiverse, individual extensions often benefit from the support of their own benefactors, which can range from enthusiastic companies to dedicated community initiatives. These supporters recognize the value an extension brings to the Quarkus ecosystem and provide resources, be it developer time, financial backing, or infrastructure, to ensure its continued development and maintenance. This decentralized sponsorship model allows for a diverse and vibrant array of extensions, each nurtured by those who most directly benefit from or believe in its specific functionality, ultimately fostering innovation and stability within the broader Quarkus community."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <div><div><div><p>
#: _includes/benefactors.html:62
msgid "You can see the individual extension supports by viewing the Community tab of the extensions' page in the <a href=\"http://quarkus.io/extensions\">Extension Catalog</a>. Take <a href=\"https://quarkus.io/extensions/io.quarkiverse.wiremock/quarkus-wiremock/?tab=community)\">Wiremock</a> as an arbitrary example."
msgstr ""
